<h2>English Version (unofficial)</h2>
<p>
The University of Geneva invites applications for
ordinary professor or associate professor in
Philosophy of Science.
</p>
<p>
<strong>Tasks</strong>: the contract is of 70% or 100%, corresponding to either 4 or 6
hours of course or seminar teaching per week. Teaching will be divided
between the BA and the MA programmes of the department of philosophy
and, perhaps, interdisciplinary and postgraduate programmes. Successful
candidates should demonstrate in their research and their teaching that:
</p>
<ul class="bullets">
    <li>they cover philosophy of science, with, if possible, a competence in the philosophy of biology</li>
    <li>they are proficient in domains of specialisation that are apt to attract students</li>
    <li>they are open to interdisciplinary research</li>
</ul>
<p>
Successful candidates will have to be active on both the national and
the international level, direct the work of students and assume
administrative and organisational duties.
</p>
<p>
<strong>Necessary Title</strong>: PhD or equivalent.<br />
<strong>Starting Date</strong>: 1st of August 2010 or another date to be decided
</p>
<p>
Please send your applications with a letter of motivation, a detailled
CV including a list of publications, a copy of the highest degree
obtained in 12 copies before APRIL 23, 2010, to:
</p>
<ul class='address'>
    <li>Secrétariat du Décanat de la Faculté des lettres</li>
    <li>Uni Bastions</li>
    <li>5, rue de Candolle</li>
    <li>CH-1211 Genève 4</li>
    <li>Switzerland</li>
</ul>
<p>
It is also at this address that you may receive more information on the
contract and its conditions.
</p>
<p>
In a perspective of equal employment, applications by women are encouraged.
</p>
</div>
